The course provides students with knowledge of different associations between sport and physical education and their role in educating physically well-educated youth. Main principles of school?s physical education class, its developments and perspectives are introduced. Parts of a class and their different variants are handled. Practical skills are acquired for teaching physical exercises.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of the course is to provide students with the survey of the role of physical education and sport in the education process and the system of school physical education.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Student who has passed the course 1) has an overview of physical education and sport as a sport science area and its role in the society; 2) is aware of the differences and similarities between physical education and sport; 3) possesses basic knowledge related to the conducting of physical education class and training class; 4) is able to apply terms and commands connected with the performing of physical exercises.
